call_score.description: Specifies the Call Score, if available. This is of type integer. Use a range of 1-5 to indicate the call experience score, with the following mapping as a reference for rating the call [5: Excellent, 4: Good, 3 : Fair, 2 : Poor, 1: Bad].

comment.description: Specifies any comments pertaining to the call. Twilio does not treat this field as PII, so no PII should be included in comments.

incident.description: Incident or support ticket associated with this call. The `incident` property is of type string with a maximum character limit of 100. Twilio does not treat this field as PII, so no PII should be included in `incident`.

parameters.name: CallSid
parameters.description: The unique string that Twilio created to identify this Call resource. It always starts with a CA.

AnsweredBy.description: Specify which entity answered the call as determined by Answering Machine Detection. Use this to provide feedback on Answering Machine Detection accuracy. Possible enumerated values, one of: `human`, `machine`. `human` indicates the call was answered by a person. `machine` indicates the call was answered by an answering machine.

ConnectivityIssue.description: Specify if the call had any connectivity issues. Possible enumerated values, one of `no_connectivity_issue`, `invalid_number`, `caller_id`, `dropped_call`, or `number_reachability`.

QualityIssues.description: Specify if the call had any subjective quality issues. Possible values, one or more of `no_quality_issue`, `low_volume`, `choppy_robotic`, `echo`, `dtmf`, `latency`, `owa`, `static_noise`. Use comma separated values to indicate multiple quality issues for the same call.

Spam.description: A boolean flag to indicate if the call was a spam call. Use this to provide feedback on whether calls placed from your account were marked as spam, or if inbound calls received by your account were unwanted spam. Use `true` if the call was a spam call.

CallScore.description: Specify the call score. This is of type integer. Use a range of 1-5 to indicate the call experience score, with the following mapping as a reference for rating the call [5: Excellent, 4: Good, 3 : Fair, 2 : Poor, 1: Bad].

Comment.description: Specify any comments pertaining to the call. `comment` has a maximum character limit of 100. Twilio does not treat this field as PII, so no PII should be included in the `comment`.

Incident.description: Associate this call with an incident or support ticket. The `incident` parameter is of type string with a maximum character limit of 100. Twilio does not treat this field as PII, so no PII should be included in `incident`.

parameters.name: From
parameters.description: A calling party. Could be an E.164 number, a SIP URI, or a Twilio Client registered name.

parameters.name: To
parameters.description: A called party. Could be an E.164 number, a SIP URI, or a Twilio Client registered name.

parameters.name: FromCarrier
parameters.description: An origination carrier.

parameters.name: ToCarrier
parameters.description: A destination carrier.

parameters.name: FromCountryCode
parameters.description: A source country code based on phone number in From.

parameters.name: ToCountryCode
parameters.description: A destination country code. Based on phone number in To.

parameters.name: Branded
parameters.description: A boolean flag indicating whether or not the calls were branded using Twilio Branded Calls.

parameters.name: VerifiedCaller
parameters.description: A boolean flag indicating whether or not the caller was verified using SHAKEN/STIR.

parameters.name: HasTag
parameters.description: A boolean flag indicating the presence of one or more [Voice Insights Call Tags](https://www.twilio.com/docs/voice/voice-insights/api/call/details-call-tags).

parameters.name: StartTime
parameters.description: A Start time of the calls. xm (x minutes), xh (x hours), xd (x days), 1w, 30m, 3d, 4w or datetime-ISO. Defaults to 4h.

parameters.name: EndTime
parameters.description: An End Time of the calls. xm (x minutes), xh (x hours), xd (x days), 1w, 30m, 3d, 4w or datetime-ISO. Defaults to 0m.

parameters.name: CallType
parameters.description: A Call Type of the calls. One of `carrier`, `sip`, `trunking` or `client`.

parameters.name: CallState
parameters.description: A Call State of the calls. One of `ringing`, `completed`, `busy`, `fail`, `noanswer`, `canceled`, `answered`, `undialed`.

parameters.name: Direction
parameters.description: A Direction of the calls. One of `outbound_api`, `outbound_dial`, `inbound`, `trunking_originating`, `trunking_terminating`.

parameters.name: ProcessingState
parameters.description: A Processing State of the Call Summaries. One of `completed`, `partial` or `all`.

parameters.name: SortBy
parameters.description: A Sort By criterion for the returned list of Call Summaries. One of `start_time` or `end_time`.

parameters.name: Subaccount
parameters.description: A unique SID identifier of a Subaccount.

parameters.name: AbnormalSession
parameters.description: A boolean flag indicating an abnormal session where the last SIP response was not 200 OK.

parameters.name: AnsweredBy
parameters.description: An Answered By value for the calls based on `Answering Machine Detection (AMD)`. One of `unknown`, `machine_start`, `machine_end_beep`, `machine_end_silence`, `machine_end_other`, `human` or `fax`.

parameters.name: AnsweredByAnnotation
parameters.description: Either machine or human.

parameters.name: ConnectivityIssueAnnotation
parameters.description: A Connectivity Issue with the calls. One of `no_connectivity_issue`, `invalid_number`, `caller_id`, `dropped_call`, or `number_reachability`.

parameters.name: QualityIssueAnnotation
parameters.description: A subjective Quality Issue with the calls. One of `no_quality_issue`, `low_volume`, `choppy_robotic`, `echo`, `dtmf`, `latency`, `owa`, `static_noise`.

parameters.name: SpamAnnotation
parameters.description: A boolean flag indicating spam calls.

parameters.name: CallScoreAnnotation
parameters.description: A Call Score of the calls. Use a range of 1-5 to indicate the call experience score, with the following mapping as a reference for the rated call [5: Excellent, 4: Good, 3 : Fair, 2 : Poor, 1: Bad].
